Glass-field thermal anomaly investigation
-1 1 3 0 65 78 5760 5500 5 2400000 0
5764 5765 5766
A Glasswalk Guide family has reported freshly fused glass in a section of the Belt that has been stable for generations, indicating new thermal fault activity. Thermal fault elementals have taken up residence at the fault ridge, vitrified sand horrors have formed from the fused material, and molten glass sentinels are preventing investigation of the anomaly zone. Eliminate one of each and report the conditions so the Guide elder can advise on route adjustment.
The thermal anomaly investigation is complete and the source creatures have been eliminated. The Guide elder's assessment confirms that a previously dormant fault has reactivated, likely due to Ninth Meridian geological drift, and has issued mandatory route adjustments for all Glasswalk Guide contracts through the affected Belt section. The anomaly report has been shared with the Scorched Wastes survey network for cross-reference.

